Being a photographer is all about curating what you see in your mind. When you first start out, there’s something called a skills gap-the work you produce is not at the quality or caliber of what you envisioned. I spent years feeling overwhelmed by the quality difference in my own images vs those I saw in magazines. The truth is, the only thing separating my work 10 years ago from today is practice. It takes 10,000 hours to even begin to master a skill, which means it took millions of photos. Millions of blurry scenes, overexposed portraits, wonky color corrections, grainy throw-a-ways.

The learning never stops. Even now, I learn something new on every shoot. When I started using @captureonepro, the game changed. Capture One Pro tethers directly to my camera and sends photos live to my computer. I can see each image on a big screen, automatically apply adjustments, check focus, show clients on a big screen, and make sure my vision is translating to the final image. 
#editwithus #captureonepro

🌼 YOUR DAZE OFF with ZOE RAIN 🌼

For the first installment in our new series about how Daze Off enthusiasts make the most of their days off, we sat down with photographer and director Zoe Rain. 

A prolific image-maker and creative, Zoe has made a name for herself as a go-to photographer for some of the biggest names in popular music, having worked with Christina Aguilera, Ed Sheeran, and many more. Her work has been published all over the world by the likes of Rolling Stone and Vanity Fair.

Zoe chatted with us while smoking Gnome World Order (Napalm OG + Wedding Mints). 

“I like to smoke we*d to get inspired” 

You can learn more about Zoe and her work at rainstudio.com.
